d poetry, music, and politics. By examining the culture of improvisation, this book reveals the ways in which Renaissance thinkers transcended cultural dichotomies, both in theory and in practice. Drawing on a wide range of sources, including letters, poetry, visual art, and philosophical texts, A Sudden Frenzy reveals the far-reaching and sometimes surprising ways that these phenomena shaped cultural developments in the Italian Renaissance and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aFolk poetry, ItalianxHistory and criticism. 0aHumanismzItaly. 0aImprovisation (Music)xHistoryy15th century. 0aItalian poetryy15th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPerformance poetryzItalyxHistory and criticism. 0aRenaissancezItaly. 0aVocal musiczItalyy15th centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aAngelo Poliziano.  aFlorence.  aItalian art.  aItalian literature.  aItaly.  aLorenzo de’ Medici.  aMarsilio Ficino.  aRenaissance literature.  aculture of improvisation.  ahumanism.  aimprovisation.  aorality.  apoetry.  apower.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148756345540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487563455423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487563455/original  a978-3-11-076715-5  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK